Package com.example.prejob.repository

Interface ArticleRepository

All Superinterfaces:
org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<Article,Long>, org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<Article,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListCrudRepository<Article,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.ListPagingAndSortingRepository<Article,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<Article,Long>, org.springframework.data.repository.query.QueryByExampleExecutor<Article>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<Article,Long>
@Repository public interface ArticleRepository extends org.springframework.data.jpa.repository.JpaRepository<Article,Long>
The ArticleRepository interface is responsible for defining the methods that can be used to interact with the underlying database for the Article entity.

The interface also declares several custom query methods to retrieve articles based on different criteria, using the @Query annotation to define the JPQL (Java Persistence Query Language) query: findAllByRoleIdAndIndustryIdAndMajorIdAndSizeId() - retrieves all articles that match the given role, industry, major, and size IDs. findAllByRoleId() - retrieves all articles that match the given role ID. findAllByRoleIdAndSizeId() - retrieves all articles that match the given role and size IDs. findAllByRoleIdAndMajorId() - retrieves all articles that match the given role and major IDs. findAllByRoleIdAndIndustryId() - retrieves all articles that match the given role and industry IDs. findAllByRoleIdAndIndustryIdAndSizeId() - retrieves all articles that match the given role, industry, and size IDs. findAllByRoleIdAndIndustryIdAndMajorId() - retrieves all articles that match the given role, industry, and major IDs.

Elena Ivanishcheva
